HEADWORD: Alyssum
<hw>A*lys"sum</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧s"s⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'a`lysson</grk>, name of a plant, perh. fr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <grk>ly`ssa</grk> raging madness.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of cruciferous plants; madwort. The
<stype>sweet alyssum</stype> (<spn>Alyssum maritimum</spn>), cultivated
for bouquets, bears small, white, sweet-scented flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

